TERMS AND CONDITIONS

0. Definitions.

  "Project" means the Ret2Shell source code, binaries, containers, build
  artifacts, and documentation, together with any modified version, fork,
  derivative work, or substantially similar commercial deployment of them.

  "Platform" means any deployment, hosted service, embedded installation,
  plugin, extension, gateway, wrapper, integration, or separate companion
  service that uses, incorporates, exposes, or materially depends on the
  Project.

  "Source Code" means the preferred form of the Project for making
  modifications, including build scripts, installation scripts, interface
  definitions, and other materials reasonably required to build, run, and
  modify the Project.

  "Operator" means any person or entity that uses, deploys, hosts, sells,
  distributes, sublicenses, or otherwise commercially exploits the Project
  or a Platform.

  "User" means any end user who uses or accesses the Platform, including
  to learn, practice, train, prepare for competitions, participate in
  courses, or otherwise consume challenge or educational content on the
  Platform, whether or not that user is enrolled in a school or formal
  educational program.

  "Verified Status" means any status showing that an account has
  completed the Operator's account-validity or eligibility process.

  "Verification Process" means any procedure used to confirm account
  validity, identity, eligibility, anti-abuse compliance, or
  organizational affiliation before granting Verified Status.

  "Organization" means any team, class, school, company, club,
  institution, community, or similar collective represented on the
  Platform.

  "Organization Resources" means challenges, writeups, notices, events,
  files, workspaces, rankings, or other resources made available
  specifically to members of an Organization.

  "User-Facing Charge" means any fee, price, tuition, subscription,
  membership, VIP or premium fee, in-app purchase, token, credit,
  deposit, package, bundle, sponsored payment, or other economic
  consideration that is requested from, targeted at, or economically
  extracted from a User in connection with that User's use of the
  Platform or related educational or challenge services. A charge remains
  User-Facing whether it is imposed directly or indirectly, whether it is
  collected by the Operator or by a third party, and whether it is
  implemented inside the Platform or through a separate service. A fee
  paid solely by a school, company, organizer, or sponsor is not
  User-Facing merely because that entity uses the Platform, unless the
  fee is separately imposed on Users or is made a condition of User
  access, User status, Organization participation, or Platform resources.

  "Private Internal Deployment" means a deployment that is not open to
  public self-registration and is limited to a defined internal
  population of a school, company, or other organization.

  "Bona Fide Educational Restriction" means a restriction imposed solely
  for curriculum sequencing, classroom management, exam integrity, age
  appropriateness, anti-abuse, or safety, and not for commercial
  advantage or private monetary gain.

  "Distribute" means to provide the Project to another person or entity
  in source form, object form, container form, or any other copyable
  form.

