5. Commercial use.

  Commercial use is allowed. This includes charging for operations,
  hosting, infrastructure, maintenance, support, customization,
  integration, migration, consulting, challenge design, challenge
  authoring, review, event preparation, event organization, sponsorship
  execution, and similar services, so long as you comply with this
  License.

6. User-Facing monetization restrictions.

  You may not, for commercial advantage or private monetary gain:
  a) create, sell, or operate paid, VIP, premium, subscription,
     membership, or equivalent feature layers for Users on the Platform,
     whether those layers are open-source or proprietary, embedded or
     external, bundled or standalone;
  b) charge Users for access to challenges, problem statements, writeups,
     learning content, practice environments, or similar educational
     resources on a Platform that permits public account registration,
     except within a Private Internal Deployment or pursuant to a Bona
     Fide Educational Restriction;
  c) sell, monetize, gate, auction, prioritize, or otherwise condition
     Verified Status or the Verification Process on payment;
  d) charge Users as a condition of joining an Organization or accessing
     Organization Resources; or
  e) use the Project or a Platform as part of a business that sells
     courses, training, tutoring, bootcamps, paid memberships, or similar
     user-facing educational products or services where User payment is
     tied to Platform access, Platform status, Organization participation,
     or Platform resources.

7. Access parity for verified users.

  On any Platform that allows public self-registration, once a user
  completes the Verification Process and obtains Verified Status, that
  user must receive ordinary non-staff challenge access rights no less
  favorable than those granted to any other user with Verified Status on
  the same Platform. Administrative, moderation, authoring, judging, and
  anti-abuse privileges are outside this rule. Non-monetized distinctions
  based solely on Bona Fide Educational Restrictions remain permitted.

8. Interpretation rules.

  The following rules apply to Sections 6 and 7:
  a) a prohibited fee remains prohibited even if it is implemented
     through an affiliate, reseller, plugin, gateway, separate domain, or
     bundled service rather than in the core codebase;
  b) open-source implementation does not make a prohibited User-Facing
     Charge permissible;
  c) separating a fee from the core Platform service does not make a
     prohibited User-Facing Charge permissible; and
  d) reasonable, non-discriminatory verification or access controls
     imposed for security, safety, anti-abuse, classroom management, or
     curriculum sequencing are allowed if they are not monetized and are
     not used as a pretext for User-Facing Charges.

9. Automatic termination and reinstatement.

  Your rights under this License terminate automatically if you violate
